page.title: 12High Street Walk cont'd
page.content: Then next to the Post Office you will see the green grocer's. This used to be a shoe mender's shop. A bit further down across the road you will see the newsagent's. This used to be a green grocer's shop. Then opposite you will see Mr Selves's ironmongers. His shop use to be a saddlery. Further down the road you will see the disused bakers. Next to the bakers is a restaurant. It has a table made of a piece of glass over the top of a well. Next to the restaurant is Lloyd's bank. The bank was once a fish and fruit shop. Next to the bank is Armada House. This was once a private house. Further down, across the street you will see the Charing Stores supermarket. This used to be another bakers. There is also a jewellers where the High Street forks.
